Logged into the server using `sudo mysql` then set a password for the root-user using the command

>
    ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED WITH mysql_native_password BY 'Olayink@79';

Started an interactive script with `sudo mysql_secure_installation`. A series interactive questions were asked, I provided a Yes answer for all.

![secure_installation](./images/secure_installation.png)

Logged into the database using `sudo mysql` and set a password for the root-user using 

>
    mysql_native_password











5. Configured MySQL server to allow connections from remote host suing the command

    >
        sudo vi /etc/mysql/mysql.conf.d/mysqld.cnf 

Replaced the `127.0.0.1` to `0.0.0.0`

